Create element by using js:
---document.createElement(‘h1’)
Create element by using react- js:
React.createElement(‘h1’)
Syntax:
React.createElaement(type,props)
Type = tagname(h1,p,div)
Prop=id,classname,onckick
reactDom.createRoot()
ReactDom.render()-method is used to diplay to the element
Syntax:
reactElement =what to render
container = where to render
a.html:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <script crossorigin src="https://unpkg.com/react@18/umd/react.production.min.js"></script>
<script crossorigin src="https://unpkg.com/react-dom@18/umd/react-dom.production.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
    <div id="root"> </div>
    <script src="a.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
a.js:
const b=React.createElement(
    'h1' ,{id:'a'}, "iam sravan"
);
const element=document.getElementById('root')
const root =ReactDOM.createRoot(element)

root.render(b)
